    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the FEA modeling framework achieves High assurance for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU. Eleven of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. Two factors (Discretization error, Test conditions) achieved one gradation below required level; the team judged these shortfalls acceptable because experimental scatter dominates total uncertainty and the single test condition is the regulatory standard. Overall evidence package supports a High assurance declaration and Accepted decision.",
